Package: SDALGCP
Title: Spatially Discrete Approximation to Log-Gaussian Cox Processes
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Olatunji", "Johnson", email = "olatunjijohnson21111@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Emanuele", "Giorgi", email = "e.giorgi@lancaster.ac.uk", role = "aut"),
    person("Peter", "Diggle", email = "p.diggle@lancaster.ac.uk", role = "aut"))
Description: Log-Gaussian Cox Processes (LGCP) has been used for aggregated count data but it is computationally intensive. Can we do better by approximating the intensity of LGCP over the region without sacrificing statistical efficiency for computational efficiency? Yes! SDA-LGCP uses Monte Carlo Maximum Likelihood and comes out to be about 5-15 times faster than LGCP model for aggregated count data.
